Initialisiert mit dev_generic_init.py v1.0.0

## Reasonprinzipien
- Jeder Agent = 1 YAML-file in `recipe/sub/`
- Agenten are Goose-Sub-Agents (no external Services)
- Communication via YAML-Structs
- Domain separation: only im eigenen Projekt-Directory write

## Agent-Typen (reference)
^| type | Task | Example |
|-----|---------|----------|
| Analyse | Data read + pattern detect | sub_research-team-analyst |
| Recovery | Aus Errorn erholen | sub_research-team-checkpoint |
| Monitoring | Monitor metrics | sub_research-team-health |
| Generator | Documents/Signale generate | sub_research-team-docgen |
| Verbetterung | Analyzen + Optimieren | sub_research-team-improver |

## YAML-Struktur
```yaml
name: sub_research-team-mein-agent
version: 1.0.0
settings:
  timeout: 120
  max_steps: 30
instructions: |
  # sub_{project}-mein-agent — 🎯 Kurzdescription
  ...
```

## Best Practices
1. **Prompts**: < 300 Zeichen
2. **Instructions**: < 2000 Zeichen
3. **⛔ Rules**: Run before each critical step
4. **Version**: always in erster line
5. **Namen**: sub_{project}-analyst

## Tools (Symlink auf MAS-Installation)
- `dev_template_generator.py` — Agenten-Generator
- `dev_rule_checker.py` — Rule-validation
- `dev_yaml_generator.py` — YAML-Generator
- `dev_workflow_runner.py` — Workflow-Execution
- `dev_goose_db.py` — Session-Analyse

## Analyse (Remote via im-* Agenten)
The im-* agents of the MAS installation can analyze your project:
```
sub_mas-im-pipeline → Verbetterungs-Pipeline
sub_mas-im-finder  → Optimierungspotential (36 Typen)
sub_mas-im-rank    → Priorisierung
sub_mas-im-designer → Patch-Draft
sub_mas-im-validator → validation
```

## Distribution
```bash
dev_build.sh --project research-team   # → standalone ZIP without MAS
```# BP-CHECKLIST.md — Best-Practices-Checklist (37 Feature-Typen A-KK)

## Settings optimization (typee A)
- [ ] A1: timeout too low? (2+ timeouts in 10 calls -> current * 1.5)
- [ ] A2: max_steps too low? (will vor Abschluss erreicht -> +10)
- [ ] A3: timeout too high? (Average < 20% timeout -> * 3)
- [ ] A4: max_steps too high? (Average < 30% max -> * 3)

## Prompt quality (Type B)
- [ ] B1: Prompt zu vage? (User asks 3x "what are you doing?")
- [ ] B2: Prompt too long? (> 500 characters)
- [ ] B3: Context missing? (Agent asks after Infos)
- [ ] B4: Prompt != Instructions? (Contradiction?)

## Instructions (typee C)
- [ ] C1: ⛔-Rule missing? (Agent tut Verbotenes)
- [ ] C2: Procedure unclear? (Agent asks for sequence/order)
- [ ] C3: Boundaries missing? (Agent oversteps scope)
- [ ] C4: referenceen outdated? (not-existente files)

## Workflow (typee D)
- [ ] D1: Step sequence wrong?
- [ ] D2: Step forgotten?
- [ ] D3: Superfluous step? (80% skipped)
- [ ] D4: Unclear question?

## Detectionspattern (typee E)
- [ ] E1: Command ohne Match?
- [ ] E2: pattern matcht wrong?
- [ ] E3: Dead detection? (> 50 sessions no match)

## Prompt-Block (typee F)
- [ ] F1: Command without prompt entry?
- [ ] F2: Sorting wrong? (Most frequent not at top)
- [ ] F3: Description unklar?
- [ ] F4: MODE-GUARD missing?

## Health (typee G)
- [ ] G1: Agent degraded? (Score < 80)
- [ ] G2: High failure rate? (> 10%)
- [ ] G3: Loops detected?
- [ ] G4: Agent dead?

## Anomalien (typee H)
- [ ] H1: Duration > 2x Average?
- [ ] H2: Tokens > 3x Average?
- [ ] H3: Kosten > 5x Average?
- [ ] H4: Session stale? (> 60min idle)

## Prompt quality (Type I)
- [ ] I1: Score < 5/10?
- [ ] I2: Identity missing? ("Who am I")
- [ ] I3: No ⛔-Boundaries?
- [ ] I4: Zu long? (> 500 characters)
- [ ] I5: Not self-contained?

## Config (typee J)
- [ ] J1: Config faulty?
- [ ] J2: Config-Value obsolete?

## Docs (typee K)
- [ ] K1: Doc outdated?
- [ ] K2: Doc missing?

## Goose (typee L)
- [ ] L1: Too many sessions?
- [ ] L2: Too many skills?
- [ ] L3: Logs too large?

## Migration (typee M)
- [ ] M1: Breaking Changes?
- [ ] M2: Non-Breaking?

## Recipe (typee N)
- [ ] N1: Duplicate recipes?
- [ ] N2: Old Version?
- [ ] N3: Missing Dependencies?

## Structure (Type O)
- [ ] O1: Instructions != Ist-State?
- [ ] O2: reference auf not-existente file?
- [ ] O3: outdateder Zaehlimpuls?
- [ ] O4: Hardcoded path?

## Tools (typee P)
- [ ] P1: Syntax-Error?
- [ ] P2: Hardcoded paths?
- [ ] P3: Import-Error?

## Calibration (typee Q)
- [ ] Q1: Oversized? (< 20% Auslastung)
- [ ] Q2: Tightly sized? (> 80% Auslastung)

## Git (typee R)
- [ ] R1: Code reduced? (positive)
- [ ] R2: Code bloated? (negative)
- [ ] R3: ⛔-Rules increased? (Safety improved)
- [ ] R4: Prompt shortened? (Token efficiency)
- [ ] R5: New file? (Only if necessary)

## Tests (typee V)
- [ ] V1: No Tests?
- [ ] V2: < 50% tested?

## Prompt-Erosion (typee GG)
- [ ] GG1: ⛔ missing im prompt?
- [ ] GG2: Version missing?
- [ ] GG3: Emoji missing?
- [ ] GG4: Prompt zu short? (< 100 characters)
- [ ] GG5: Instructions too long? (> 2000 characters)

## Drift (typee FF + JJ)
- [ ] FF1: timeout deviating?
- [ ] FF2: max_steps deviating?
- [ ] JJ1: Installation deviating?

## Backup (typee HH)
- [ ] HH1: > 50 Backup-directoryse?
- [ ] HH2: > 100 .bak-files?
- [ ] HH3: No backup before change?
- [ ] HH4: Backup > 30 days old?

## Monitoring (typee Y + CC + DD)
- [ ] Y1: Recovery slower?
- [ ] CC1: OOM/MemoryError?
- [ ] DD1: Tool not found?version: 1.0.0
title: '{EMOJI} SUB-MAS-{NAME} — {DESCRIPTION}'
description: 'v1.0.0 | MAS-internal: {TASK}'
instructions: "# sub_mas-{name} — {EMOJI} {Title}\n\nMAS-ENGINEER-internal. Responsible for {TASK}.\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## SOT-RULES (centrally maintained)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{SOT_RESTRICTIONS}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## HARDENING (Methods 5+6+9+10+1)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{SOT_ENFORCEMENT}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## RECOVERY-SYSTEM (5 levels)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{SOT_RECOVERY}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## SIGNALS\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{SOT_SIGNALS}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## AUTONOMY MODE (UNTOUCHABLE)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{BP_AUTONOMY}\n\nThe Agent runs INDEPENDENT — no user intervention needed.\n\nDECISION TREE (at each Task):\n   Is the goal reached? → return mas_result\n   Error occurred? → Retry (Level 1-4)\n   max_actions reached? → Continue actively (not cancel)\n   Timeout? → Reduce sub-steps, try again\n   In loop (3× same Task)? → Find alternative\n   User does not respond? → Show progress + ask again\n\nRETRY-ESKALATION (4 Levels):\n   Level 1: Try different path (Bash → Python → Sub-Agent)\n   Level 2: Reduce (fewer files, smaller steps, Focus)\n   Level 3: Restart with doubled max_turns (fresh context)\n   Level 4: Escalate to User with more precise question + suggestion\n\nLOOP-DETECTION:\n   Same Task 3× in succession? → Level 2 (Alternative)\n   Same User-question 2×? → Force clarification\n   Tokens per step increasing? → Reduce complexity\n   No progress after 5 steps? → Level 3 (restart)\n\nPROGRESS-TRACKING:\n   After EACH step: \"Status: X/Y done. Next: {next_step}\"\n   At max_turns reached: Continue actively, ask \"Should I continue?\"\n   At User \"yes\": max_turns=500 new start and continue (NO restart)\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## DOMAIN SEPARATION\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{BP_SEPARATION}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## 🛠️ TOOL INVENTORY (explicit)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n✅ HAS: load (load knowledge), delegate (start Sub-Agent)\n✅ HAS: bash, python3 (Shell-Execution)\n✅ HAS: cat, write, edit, grep (File-I/O)\n❌ DOES NOT HAVE: read (fails in 40% of cases — use cat instead)\n❌ DOES NOT HAVE: network (only if explicitly approved)\n\nORDER:\n   1. python3 (dev_*.py) — primary\n   2. bash (shell) — secondary\n   3. Sub-Agent (delegate) — ONLY for Analysis (Sub-agent has no shell)\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## ⛔ SAFETY-RULES (at least 6)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n⛔ NEVER Framework-Concepts as MAS-Concepts designate\n⛔ NEVER Framework-Agents delegate (executor, planner, controller, starter)\n⛔ NEVER MAS-Tools copy to Framework-Directories\n⛔ NEVER give up — always Find alternative (Retry Levels 1-4)\n⛔ ALWAYS Backup before Changes (dev_editor.py task=BACKUP)\n⛔ ALWAYS validate YAML after edit (python3 -c 'yaml.safe_load(...)')\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## BEST-PRACTICES (auto-apply)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{BP_STRUCTURE}\n\n{BP_PROMPT}\n\n{BP_SETTINGS}\n\n{BP_RECOVERY}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## OPEN IMPROVEMENTS (from improvement-plan)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n{IMPROVEMENT_NOTES}\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## 📥 INPUT (from MAS-Engineer)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nThe MAS-Engineer passes these parameters via delegate():\n\n```yaml\nagent_intake:\n  signal: '🟣 HANDOVER'\n  request_id: string (UUID)\n  from: 'dev-mas-engineer'\n  to: 'sub_mas-{name}'\n  task: string ({TASK}|...)\n  workspace: string (Path to the Workspace)\n  state_path: string (optional, Path to the .state-file)\n```\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## 📤 OUTPUT (MAS-native — NOT Framework-Format)\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n```yaml\nmas_result:\n  signal: '🟢 DONE' | '🟣 HANDOVER' | '🟠 BLOCKED' | '🔴 ERROR'\n  request_id: '<original_request_id>'\n  from: 'sub_mas-{name}'\n  to: 'dev-mas-engineer'\n  status: 'success' | 'error' | 'timeout'\n  observations:\n    - severity: 'P1' | 'P2' | 'P3'\n      title: string\n      description: string\n  summary: string\n```\n\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n## 📋 PROCEDURE\n## ════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSTEP 1 — Validate input:\n  Check: signal='🟣 HANDOVER', request_id exists, task is valid\n  IF faulty → mas_result: signal='🔴 ERROR', status='error'\n\nSTEP 2 — Execute task:\n  EXECUTE {TASK} according to task-parameters through\n  Use dev_*.py Tools (Python-First)\n  At problems: Retry-Eskalation (Levels 1-4)\n\nSTEP 3 — Result check:\n  Completeness? Correctness? Quality?\n  IF OK → mas_result: signal='🟢 DONE', status='success'\n  IF partial → mas_result: signal='🟠 BLOCKED', status='partial'\n\nSTEP 4 — Output:\n  Structured YAML-Output (see Output-Schema above)\n\n### Edge Cases\n- Tool not available → Level 1: Try different path\n- Timeout → Level 2: Reduce sub-steps, try again\n- max_actions reached → Continue actively, ask \"Should I continue?\"\n- Repeated Error → Level 3: Restart with more max_turns\n- Data inconsistent → Level 4: Escalate to User with more precise question\n- Result incomplete → Partial result with status='partial'\n- YAML-Output faulty → \"❌ Output-Format-Error: {detail}\"\n- Workspace does not exist → \"❌ Workspace not found: {workspace}\"\n"
